                   <h3 class="sol">A kind-hearted note (actually, two) about<br>
my intentions in creating this program:</h3>
<div class="ta-left">
<p><span class="sol">FIRST,</span> <em>Feast</em> is NOT a diet program nor is it intended to help women lose weight. Therefore, if you are hoping to or counting on losing weight with this program, this is not the program for you. <em>Feast</em> is about coming home to ourselves, our bodies, and our hungers. <em>Feast</em> celebrates the broad diversity of body sizes in the world and acknowledges that health exists across the body size-spectrum. The long-term outcome of the provided practices is often a return to one’s set-point weight. For some this will be higher than their current weight and for others it will be lower and for some it will result in no change at all. Regardless, weight change is not a goal of <em>Feast</em>, rather this course is for women who have begun to understand that their happiness and wellbeing is not dependent on a number on the scale.</p>
<p><span class="sol">SECOND,</span> <em>Feast</em> is designed for women who are prepared to make space in their lives to fully participate in the program. It will be an intensive three months, designed with the feel of spaciousness and plenty of integration time. The limited spaces in this program are meant for women who are ready now… those who are willing, and able to create time in their schedule to dedicate to doing the work and connecting with others on the same path.</p>
</div>
<p>It’s a radical act for a woman to choose a life of feast, rather than a life of famine.</p>
<h4 class="section-last-line" style="margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: -10px;">Is now the&nbsp;time&nbsp;you make this choice?</h4>
