            <section class="section14 section" id="faq">
                <div class="container-fluid">
                    <div class="sec14-h-wrap">
                        <h3 class="sec14-h">Frequently Asked Questions</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="row">

                            <ul id="faqlist">

                            <li class="faq">
                                <h3 class="subtitle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#0" aria-expanded="false">
                                    <span class="plus"></span> <p>HOW MANY SPACES ARE AVAILABLE IN <i>FEAST</i>?</p>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="collapse" id="0">
                  <p>There is space for up to 30 women.</p>
                </div>
                            </li>

                            <li class="faq">
                                <h3 class="subtitle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#1" aria-expanded="false">
                                    <span class="plus"></span> <p>HOW WILL YOU DECIDE WHO FILLS THOSE SPACES?</p>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="collapse" id="1">
                  <p><i>Feast</i> will be filled on a first come, first apply basis assuming applicants are a good fit. <i>Feast</i> always fills quickly, so if you want to come on the journey, do not delay in submitting your application.</p>
                </div>
                            </li>

                            <li class="faq">
                                <h3 class="subtitle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#2" aria-expanded="false">
                                    <span class="plus"></span> <p>WHY DO I HAVE TO APPLY?</p>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="collapse" id="2">
                  <p><i>Feast</i> is by application only because I want to ensure that every woman who joins this intimate circle is a good match for the journey ahead. Not every woman is ready for <i>Feast</i> and the application process helps to ensure the right fit.</p>
                </div>
                            </li>

                            <li class="faq">
                                <h3 class="subtitle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#3" aria-expanded="false">
                                    <span class="plus"></span> <p>I HAVE AN EATING DISORDER—CAN THIS PROGRAM HELP ME?</p>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="collapse" id="3">
                  <p><i>Feast</i> is not a substitute for the medical and psychological treatment that eating disorders require. If you have an eating disorder and want to be a part of <i>Feast</i> as an adjunct to ongoing treatment, you’ll be asked to disclose this in your application and I will need to speak with your primary therapist for approval before acceptance will be granted.</p>
                </div>
                            </li>

                            <li class="faq">
                                <h3 class="subtitle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#4" aria-expanded="false">
                                    <span class="plus"></span> <p>I WON’T BE ABLE TO ATTEND SOME/ALL OF THE LIVE CALLS, WILL I STILL BE ABLE TO GET ALL I NEED FROM <i>FEAST</i>?</p>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="collapse" id="4">
                  <p>The live calls will be offered at two different times to make them as accessible as possible for women in different time zones and with conflicting schedules. That said, attendance on the live calls is not a requirement. All the calls will be recorded and the discussion topics will also be explored on the private Facebook page.</p>
                </div>
                            </li>

                            <li class="faq">
                                <h3 class="subtitle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#5" aria-expanded="false">
                                    <span class="plus"></span> <p>I MAY NOT BE ABLE TO KEEP UP WITH THE COURSE DUE TO WORK, TRAVEL, OR FAMILY REASONS. IF I MISS A WEEK WILL THE MATERIAL BE ACCESSIBLE FOR A WHILE?</p>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="collapse" id="5">
                  <p>Yes, all the materials are available for you to download and study or review at your leisure. Missing a week and catching yourself up is not a problem. Though missing more than that might be an interference in your learning.</p>
                </div>
                            </li>

                            <li class="faq">
                                <h3 class="subtitle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#6" aria-expanded="false">
                                    <span class="plus"></span> <p>I WANT TO JOIN <i>FEAST</i> BUT I CAN’T AFFORD IT. IS THERE ANY WAY AROUND THIS?</p>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="collapse" id="6">
                  <p>If you’ve heard the saying “If you give a woman a fish she eats for a day. If you teach her to catch a fish, she eats for life,” then you might understand why <i>Feast</i> is so valuable. This is an opportunity to learn how to fish. <i>Feast</i> is an investment in your freedom. <i>Feast</i> is also a financial investment and the price reflects the profound shifts participants can expect to achieve. </p>
<p>If you’re interested in joining <i>Feast</i> but not in a position to do so at the moment, the program will be offered again in 2018. I invite you to save your resources to invest then.</p>
                </div>
                            </li>

                            <li class="faq">
                                <h3 class="subtitle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#7" aria-expanded="false">
                                    <span class="plus"></span> <p>I’M NOT GREAT WITH COMPUTERS, DO I NEED ANY SPECIAL EQUIPMENT OR SKILLS TO PARTICIPATE EASILY?</p>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="collapse" id="7">
                  <p><i>Feast</i> is very simple. You will need an email address, Facebook account, and the ability to read PDF files and listen to Mp3 recordings. You will also need to be able to join into our live group calls via telephone or over the internet. A journal and pen will come in handy, too.</p>
                </div>
                            </li>

                            <li class="faq">
                                <h3 class="subtitle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#8" aria-expanded="false">
                                    <span class="plus"></span> <p>WHAT IF I’M NOT ON FACEBOOK?</p>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="collapse" id="8">
                  <p>Participants will need to have a Facebook account in order to participant in the private Facebook group and gain access to important information shared there, but Facebook participation outside of <i>Feast's</i> private group is entirely optional. </p>
                </div>
                            </li>

                            <li class="faq">
                                <h3 class="subtitle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#9" aria-expanded="false">
                                    <span class="plus"></span> <p>I’VE NEVER TAKEN AN ONLINE COURSE; WILL I BE ABLE TO LEARN THIS WAY?</p>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="collapse" id="9">
                  <p>Online learning isn’t necessarily harder than in-person learning, but it is different. A huge benefit of the virtual nature of <i>Feast</i> is that you and I don’t have to live in the same town in order for us to intimately connect and for you to learn. You can also participate in the course from your home, office, or favorite coffee shop. And for the most part, you can also engage in learning during the time of day that works best for you. </p>
<p>I have taught extensively in-person and virtually. One of my gifts is the ability to create intimacy, trust, and community through online learning. If you show up to read, explore, listen, reflect, practice and discuss the material each week you will have no trouble maximizing your learning.</p>
                </div>
                            </li>

                            <li class="faq">
                                <h3 class="subtitle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#10" aria-expanded="false">
                                    <span class="plus"></span> <p>HOW MUCH TIME WILL THIS COURSE TAKE ON A WEEKLY BASIS?</p>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="collapse" id="10">
                  <p>Applicants should expect to invest between three and five hours each week participating in <i>Feast</i> . Some of this time is simply practicing new skills or actively observing yourself as you live your everyday life. Some of the time is spent in meditation, listening to lessons and interviews, writing reflections in your journal, reading the assigned materials, and participating in the live calls. Like most things in life, the more you invest in <i>Feast</i> , the more you will get out of it.</p>
                </div>
                            </li>

                            <li class="faq">
                                <h3 class="subtitle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#11" aria-expanded="false">
                                    <span class="plus"></span> <p>WHEN WILL <i>FEAST</i> BE OFFERED AGAIN?</p>
                                </h3>
                                <div class="collapse" id="11">
                  <p><i>Feast</i> will be offered again in 2018.</p>
                </div>
